# Skull

> The skull is composed of **22 bones** — 8 neurocranium bones encasing the brain and 14 viscerocranium bones forming the facial skeleton.

## 🔗 Connected Structures
- [[Vertebral Column]] — Occipital bone articulates with Atlas (C1) at the **atlanto-occipital joint**
- [[Mandible]] — Temporal bone articulates with the mandible at the **temporomandibular joint (TMJ)** — the only freely movable facial joint

## 🔗 Associated Muscles
- [[Masseter]] — Inserts on the mandible; closes the jaw
- [[Sternocleidomastoid]] — Inserts on the mastoid process; flexes/rotates neck
- [[Trapezius]] — Originates from the occipital bone

## 🗂️ Component Bones

### Neurocranium — 8 bones
| Bone | Count | Location |
|------|-------|----------|
| Frontal bone | 1 | Forehead |
| Parietal bone | 2 | Top of skull |
| Temporal bone | 2 | Sides (temples) |
| Occipital bone | 1 | Back of skull |
| Sphenoid bone | 1 | Central cranial base |
| Ethmoid bone | 1 | Anterior cranial base |

### Viscerocranium — 14 bones
| Bone | Count |
|------|-------|
| Nasal bone | 2 |
| Maxilla | 2 |
| Zygomatic bone | 2 |
| Lacrimal bone | 2 |
| Palatine bone | 2 |
| Inferior nasal concha | 2 |
| Vomer | 1 |
| [[Mandible]] | 1 |

## 📐 Major Sutures
- **Coronal suture** — Frontal ↔ Parietal bones
- **Sagittal suture** — Parietal ↔ Parietal bones
- **Lambdoid suture** — Parietal ↔ Occipital bone
- **Squamous suture** — Temporal ↔ Parietal bones

## 🔑 Key Foramina
| Foramen | Contents |
|---------|----------|
| [[Foramen Magnum]] | Brainstem → spinal cord, vertebral arteries |
| Optic canal | Optic nerve (CN II) |
| Jugular foramen | CN IX, X, XI + internal jugular vein |

## 🏥 Clinical Significance
- **[[Mastoid Process]]** — easily palpable behind ear; [[Sternocleidomastoid]] insertion
- **[[Sella Turcica]]** — houses pituitary gland in sphenoid bone
- **[[Cribriform Plate]]** — CN I olfactory filaments pass through ethmoid bone
- **Skull fractures** — Linear vs. depressed fractures
- **Raised intracranial pressure (ICP)** — Anterior fontanelle bulges in infants before suture closure
- **Temporomandibular disorder (TMD)** — Jaw pain, clicking
- **Anterior fontanelle** — Closes around 18 months of age


